body:
`$size(interface_array)` doesn't work currently. Would be nice to have it.

## Example
```systemverilog
interface intf;
    logic a;
endinterface


module t (
    input v_clk
);
    intf intf_array [3:0]();
    initial begin
        $display("size:%d", $size(intf_array));
    end

endmodule
```
## Error
```
%Error: t.sv:11:35: Found definition of 'intf_array' as a CELL but expected a variable
   11 |         $display("size:%d", $size(intf_array));
      |                                   ^~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```
